DUST DEVIL chased three to four wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, spun three wide for home, proved no match for the top one while running on to secure the place honors. OPTIC WAY chased four then three wide under a ride from the three-eighths, angled five wide into upper stretch, stayed on one paced to the finish. ALCOOLS broke out at the start under coaxing, showed the way in hand three then two wide under pressure from NO BURN to the outside, yielded the front near the three-eighths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch and weakened. DADDY KNOWS chased just off the inside under a firm left grip head cocked to the infield down the backstretch, got taken in hand briefly half a mile from home, then floated two then three wide when getting out nearing the midway point on the turn, went eight wide into upper stretch under urging and weakened. BLACK BELT chased five then four wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, swung four wide into upper stretch, tired. HAMMERIN AAMER coaxed from the gate, chased two to three wide down the backstretch and then three to four wide through the turn under coaxing from three furlongs out, spun three wide for home and tired. MOUNT TRAVERS chased along the inside under a ride from the three-eighths and tired in the stretch. LOST IN ROME coaxed from the start, chased five to six wide under a ride from midway on the turn, continued six wide at the head of the stretch, and tired through to the finish.
